The paper focuses on the development of a new two-stage convolutional neural network architecture for hand gesture recognition, which involves accurate pixel-level semantic segmentation to determine the hand regions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of multimedia techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the development of a system for human-computer interaction, which suggests that it could belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
